The Karnataka Police has come under heavy criticism for what many says was 'excessive action' after the principal and parent of school students were arrested on charges of sedition for staging an anti-CAA play in the school.

On Thursday, Fareeda Begum, the in-charge of the Shaheen Group of Institutions, a school in Bidar's primary section and the mother of a Class VI student, were arrested by the police after they were booked under sedition for allegedly insulting PM Narendra Modi.

According to reports, the play, which criticized the CAA was staged by the student in the school on January 21 and had a dialogue insulting the PM. The case was filed on Monday by some right wing activists after the videos of it went viral on social media.

Nilesh Rakshala, an activist of the Akhil Bharatiya Vidyarthi Parishad who made the complaint said children are being used to spread propaganda against CAA, NRC and insult the PM.

