The arrest of the school teacher and parent is in sharp contrast to what the Karnataka Police did just a month back when students of a school in Dakshina Kannada district reenactment of the Babri mosque demolition on its annual sports day.

Puducherry Lt Governor Kiran Bedi and Union Minister for Chemical and Fertilisers D V Sadananda Gowda were among the dignitaries who attended the event. Kiran Bedi had even tweeted about the show and praised the students' performance. She said they should get a chance to showcase their talent at the republic day celebrations in New Delhi.

